INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('15175','2','1066','Subproducts option','- For the product BIN (id 77) they want the product to be specified in some subproducts:\r\n* Luchtmonsters\r\n* Contactmonsters\r\n* Moment opname temperatuur\r\n* Moment opname Co2\r\n* Moment opname relatieve luchtvochtigheid\r\n\r\nWhat does this mean? Well in the offer product text for this product (BIN / ID77), in some text they want to specify this product. So if they sell 33 x BIN. They want to specify it like this:\r\n- 30 x Luchtmonsters\r\n- 0 x Contactmonsters\r\n- 1 x Moment opname temperatuur\r\n- 2 x moment opname Co2\r\n- 0 x moment opname relatieve luchtvochtigheid\r\n\r\nThis is to show it in the offer description text (second page) for this product. Then the question is, where we gonna specify this. I think the best is, that when we are in project/offer edit screen, and we select product BIN that there will come extra input fields (instead of ammount). So it can be specified there. Also this specified products must be visible for planning and worksheets. So that outside workers and planning know what subproducts are inside product BIN. In invoice then can be just 33 x BIN. Specifcation is only for Offer in that case.\r\nso in planning, reports, invoices, they are all intogether? Only difference is in offer text and when editing project? Also, this is for this product only?\r\nIn reports, invoices, it will show just like 33 x BIN, in planning(incl. agenda overview), worksheets, offers, it will show specified. Its for only the product BIN, yes.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','7','504','990','7','2011-04-05 04:40:22','2011-04-19 18:07:57','2011-04-05','0','4','15145','15145','14','15','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('15176','2','1066','Add colored box with status in agenda events, fluid layout for agenda view','- Also in the agenda overview, somehow would be great if they instantly could see the status of a subproject. So planning department knows without clicking, the status of a project. Maybe we can achive this with Balloon tips or using different colors? You have suggestions?\r\nHow long usually projects? if several hours, maybe add status on it? Or just add colored square on the right like  _______________   with padding and rounded. But with thinner events, can be not very good. Actually, for planning, I think fixed page width is not good.\r\nMaybe we can add a square box, in listing top like:\r\n\r\nSo a colored round square box in right top, with color+letter (U for Uitgevoerd, for example)\r\nWhat you think? Also you think its good to make planning page fluid (width). So if it maximizes the width based on screen width?\r\nyeah, I think both is good\r\nokay lets do it.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','5','504','990','4','2011-04-05 04:44:30','2011-04-22 21:08:02','2011-04-05','0','2','9313','9313','50','51','0');
