INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('16716','1','1066','Fix-list','- Planning time: This bug i already explained. When planning in item, it plans in one hour later. Timezone bug i think.\r\n- When in worksheets they want to send Monsterform, but Monsterform. has no data, it gives now error message. This message must translated to:\r\n--------> Geen monsterwaardes aanwezig. Het monsterformulier kan niet worden verzonden. <----------\r\n- In invoice template empty locations shouldn\'t be visible there, if they have no subprojects. Same for offers template.\r\n- For invoices: Don\'t accept entering payment higher then the invoice sum. So if the open ammount is 500, and somebody wants to pay 600. it should give error.\r\n- For simultaneous sorting in planning overview, the date goes before the distance. So that date\'s are always sorted from ascending/descending or vice versa\r\n- In reports overview when changing report status (complete/sent), on save it will not remember the filtered overview. So if we want to see all \'expired\' reports, and change one of the listings status, on save, it goes back to basic overview (doesn\'t remember filtered overview)\r\n- For Sales usergroup: In agenda right now they can only view items. Not edit. For the new feature \'Day items\', we must set them also read only (so no popup click for editing)\r\n- For Sales usergroup: Make also Reports module available for them. And also give them the dropdown sorting to show \'By me\' or \'All\' items.\r\n- Monsterform autosave now works, only the date text is not visible. I think text too long.\r\n- In worksheets overview they can send monsterform. There in the text they want an extra variable: {Subproject code}. This to show in e-mail text, the subproject code where this monsterform belongs to.\r\n- Admin-only: THey want that only admin usergroup can change user names/passwords.\r\n- In planning when we search by company (for example Brancom) and then select from dropdown a status, it shows different clients in overview. So it\'s a bug.\r\n- In planning agenda view, it doesn\'t show calender picker. Tested in Firefox and Chrome.\r\n- Also in planning agenda, when setting startdate for example 26 april, system automatically must preset for enddate also 26 april. So they don\'t have to changed this all the time.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','6','504','990','10','2011-04-27 01:21:04','2011-05-04 21:25:04','2011-04-27','0',NULL,NULL,'16716','1','2','0');
