INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('19322','2','1066','Clarify how length/frequency values should work','Currently it works this way:\r\nwhen subproject frequency is set, this defines total number of occurrences per year. So for monthly it\'s 12, for yearly it\'s 1 and for weekly it\'s 52.\r\nThis means, total work done will be the same as it was in offer. So payment is the same. And number of occurrences is the same for same frequencies, so it\'s stable.\r\nBut as a result we can\'t change frequency, because there is no easy and reliable way to recount total number of occurrences in general case. \r\nAlso it\'s not guaranteed that subproject will be finished in a full year. Because start dates can be changed. And next occurrence in weekly subprojects will be created in a week after previous. With a total number of 52 occurrences.\r\n\r\nOther option is to create next occurrence after a week/month/etc. after previous occurrence\'s start date and check if it\'s within subproject length. So in case of weekly subproject, for example, this maybe 50 occurrences, but if next occurrence should be done after length is over, it will not be done, and the rest too. So subproject will end no matter how much actual occurrences were made, but depending on date. \r\nAs result, we can change frequency freely, but total number of occurrences (and invoiced total) will be different from offer.\r\n\r\nSo I would suggest to discuss this issue with the client, which way is preferred.\r\n\r\nEstimated time is my quote in case you want to switch to second scenario.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','7','504','990','4','2011-05-27 15:26:22','2011-08-31 04:18:49','2011-05-27','0','4',NULL,'19322','1','2','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('19331','1','1066','Definition of \'When all subprojects are done\' setting','*Yuri, client gave this comment:*\r\n\r\n_Regarding the definition of the function \"If all subprojects are done\" for the grouping reports function in the project settings:\r\n \r\nThis function is used to generate a combined report once all the corresponding sub-projects are done in the relevant period. If a project is ongoing, eg half yearly output, the system should generate a report half yearly.\r\n \r\nThis should be implemented as soon as possible._ \r\n\r\n\r\nWhat should we do, or communicate? I think what they mean is, that when they set grouping reports to \'if all subproject are done\', it should look at the subprojects frequency to generate a report. Or else it would wait till all subprojects are done in that year, but that\'s too long waiting. What you think?\r\n\r\n\r\n*Also one more comment from client:*\r\n\r\n_And I would like to know the following:\r\n \r\nAre there any projects in a similar position as SubProjects 222-A till E.? So projects that have been performed but for which no report is generated because the system is \"waiting\" in the second round which takes place later? (So till all subprojects are done) If so, these should be generated as soon as possible, because otherwise we get into trouble with reporting / billing. We can not control themselves, I do not know if you can re-check the database or something and where necessary, correct things?\r\n\r\nAlso if this \'if all subprojects are done\' setting is change/fixed, does it also apply for existing projects? So that they will report the right way (with new fix). If not, then all project with this setting, should be fixed/update._\r\n\r\n\r\n*Yuri let me know if any questions.*',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','7',NULL,'1561','17','2011-05-27 18:14:03','2011-08-18 18:56:29','2011-05-27','0','2',NULL,'19331','1','2','0');
