INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('19866','2','1066','Planning: Plan in subproject cycles immedeatly for a given period','They want to have a feature in planning, to plan in a subproject wich is planned in on the same day, immedeatly on a period on the same date/time\r\nthey have this product \'SPOELEN\'  wich is done weekly. Right now they loose alot of time, planning this weekly on same day/time\r\nwould be great, if they could plan in immedeatly some cycles ahead\r\nmaybe that they even can see 1/9 til 9/9 plan in on every friday, starting from 1-09-2011. Of course then they also set for wich employer they plan this occurences.\r\n\r\n\r\nYuri: Maybe button \'plan in next occurences same way\'? Maybe text value to enter how may occurrences to plan ahead\r\n\r\nMichel: Maybe we can show an inputbox with: Plan in .../9\r\nso they can see wich cycles in total, and of course they can only input the cycles wich are not done yet',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','6',NULL,'1561','21','2011-06-03 23:26:00','2011-08-18 18:56:29','2011-06-03','0','2',NULL,'19866','1','2','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('19870','2','1066','Planning: Plan in selected subprojects with time interval','yuri, they want to be able to select a few subprojects and plan them in for the same employer. For this they want to indicate a start time, from wich it must start planning and the timeframe (per subproject). So for example 30 minutes, 1 hour etc.. So that system will plan this subprojects in based on starttime and interval time\r\n\r\n\r\nYuri:  hmm, so they select several subprojects and it puts them in schedule one-by-one with given length?\r\n\r\n\r\nMichel:  yes\r\nso for example they set date 1/9/2011 - 09:00 as startdate. And interval per subproject:\r\n\r\n2011.34-A - 30 min\r\n2011.34-B - 30 min\r\n2011.54-A - 2 hours\r\n\r\nso in the end we have planned:\r\n\r\n2011.34-A - 09.00\r\n2011.34-B - 09.30\r\n2011.54-A - 10.00\r\nand if there was one more, the next one would start 12:00\r\n\r\n\r\n Yuri:  hmm, maybe add length to subprojects in project editor? It probably won\'t vary too much? Maybe even put it to product to use initial value from autocomplete?\r\n\r\n\r\nMichel:  that would be good. But have to consult with client how to want it implemented. To specify it on forehand per subproject, or product, or not...\r\n\r\n\r\n Yuri:  I think there can be a tab in \'Subprojects planning\' section with this feature. Also, if planning goes beyond end of work day, continue on next one?\r\n\r\n\r\nMichel:  hmm, then we have to define what is a \' working day \'\r\ni think for now would be good if they can see, till what time it will be planned, according to the settings\r\nso if they see that with current chosen subprojects it will plan in till 19:00\r\nit will show \'With current settings it will plan in till 19:00;\r\nwhat you think\r\n\r\n\r\n Yuri:  sure',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','6',NULL,'1561','17','2011-06-03 23:41:47','2011-08-18 18:56:30','2011-06-03','0','6',NULL,'19870','1','2','0');
