INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('21461','1','2379','Small adjustment in Main.css file. ','Feedback from client:\r\n\r\nThe DIV for the login has a fixed margin, wich looks good in a browser with a standard resolution screen. But on a netbook it looks not so good. Could you change the margin from 268px to 10%? This because monday 27th they want to test system also on some netbooks. \r\n\r\n*Michel: Let me know if you can fix this before monday.*\r\n\r\nHere the exact information:\r\n\r\nrow: 713\r\n\r\nmargin: 10% auto 0;',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','7',NULL,'1561','5','2011-06-23 21:34:29','2011-06-30 05:43:32','2011-06-23','0',NULL,NULL,'21461','1','2','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('21462','2','2379','Targets per branch, per day','*Michel:*\r\n_- Right now they set per Branch the target. This is a fixed target wich is always used. But want they want, is to set this per day. So everyday they want to be able to set a different target per branch/store location. I think the best would be to have an extra \'tab\' on the leftmenu with \'Branch targets\'. So they can set per day the targets. Also they want to be able to import these targets with an Excel file (XLS)._\r\n\r\n\r\n*Bartosz:*\r\nNot sure I understood it correctly, but they want to have a possibility to set different target per branch per day. So they click on the \"Branch targets\" menu and then select a branch, then select a day and set a target for this particular branch and day. Is that right?\r\n*Michel: Yes. Although most values will be automatically imported with a file. Also in the branch editor pop-up box, we should add a tab \'Targets\'. So they can also see it there.*\r\n\r\n\r\nThen they can review the targets for each day for a branch and change it, if needed?\r\n*Michel: Yes*\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat about the situation when for a particular branch and day there\'s no custom target defined in the \"Branch targets\" tab? Should the target be taken from the \"default\" branch target field, provided on the edit branch screen?\r\n*Michel: No, this field we will remove from there. If no value set, we use standard value \'0\'*\r\n\r\n\r\nRegarding the import - what format will be the excel file? Can it be a CSV file instead of excel file or it must be XLS?\r\n*Michel: XLS is more easy for customer. If it\'s to complex we have to use CSV. Client in that case has to export self to CSV. But sometimes this exporting step gives problems. That\'s why i suggested XLS. Let me know.*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure if I will be able to finish it before 27th. Can it be 28th, Tuesday?\r\nPlease let me know if it\'s ok for you.\r\n*Michel: Would be great if we could do it for the 27th. If it\'s really not possible/unrealistic let me know.*\r\n\r\nI will give you tonight a import example file. The file will have tabs in the excelsheet. Every tab has as a name the Branchnummer. More info will follow here on this issue.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','6',NULL,'1561','12','2011-06-23 22:11:01','2011-09-02 23:03:22','2011-06-23','0',NULL,NULL,'21462','1','2','0');
