INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('21901','2','2379','Planning: Add weeknumbers','In planning > agenda overview we must add the week numbers for the \'week\' view. Right now we have text:\r\n\r\n27 June - 3 July 2011\r\n\r\nWe should add it in front like:\r\n\r\nWK34 - 27 June - 3 July 2011\r\n',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','6',NULL,'1561','3','2011-06-28 20:02:22','2011-07-05 05:37:11','2011-06-28','0',NULL,NULL,'21901','1','2','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('21908','2','2379','Planning employer> Plan in immedeatly for a week','They want in the planning screen, where they plan in an employer, that they can see all days of week for a specific Weeknumber. Then for every day of the week the can indicate from wich start to endtime he/she will work, enable/disable if this is a vacation and add a comment. So actually what we have now, but then not per day, but for 7 days. So it would look like this:\r\n\r\nAgendapicker > Pick 28th june > Display: WK34 - 27th june - 3 july 2011\r\nMon 27 - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nTue 28 - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nWed 29 - etc..\r\nThu 30 - etc..\r\nFri 1 - etc..\r\nSat 2 - etc..\r\nSun 3 - etc..\r\n\r\nThis way they can plan more easily. Also when they press \'schedule\'  to save this planning, it should redirect to the agenda view, for the planned item\'s date (first date value at least), and set the branch/employer filter settings in overview from the planned values.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','5',NULL,'1561','5','2011-06-28 20:12:53','2011-07-15 03:11:42','2011-06-28','0',NULL,NULL,'21908','1','2','0');
INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES ('21909','2','2379','Planning: List to search people outside branch','Bartek, we have discussed this. So we add an extra dropdown (with filter function) where they can select a person outside the branch to plan in. So then we have two dropdowns in planning:\r\n\r\n- Employee list, showing employers from selected branch\r\n- Employee list with all employers, but with filter option.\r\n\r\nI think maybe we should add a checkbox \'Plan somebody outside this branch\'. So after they selected a branch, and enabled the checkbox \'Plan somebody outside this branch\' it will disable first dropdown and enable the full employee list with filter.',NULL,NULL,'5','1561','5',NULL,'1561','6','2011-06-28 20:15:55','2011-09-02 23:19:15','2011-06-28','0',NULL,NULL,'21909','1','2','0');
