INSERT INTO `journal_details` VALUES ('48827','40796','attr','description','They want in the planning screen, where they plan in an employer, that they can see all days of week for a specific Weeknumber. Then for every day of the week the can indicate from wich start to endtime he/she will work, enable/disable if this is a vacation and add a comment. So actually what we have now, but then not per day, but for 7 days. So it would look like this:\r\n\r\nAgendapicker > Pick 28th june > Display: WK34 - 27th june - 3 july 2011\r\nMon - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nTue - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nWed - etc..\r\nThu - etc..\r\nFri - etc..\r\nSat - etc..\r\nSun - etc..\r\n\r\nThis way they can plan more easily. Also when they press \'schedule\'  to save this planning, it should redirect to the agenda view, for the planned item\'s date (first date value at least), and set the branch/employer filter settings in overview from the planned values.','They want in the planning screen, where they plan in an employer, that they can see all days of week for a specific Weeknumber. Then for every day of the week the can indicate from wich start to endtime he/she will work, enable/disable if this is a vacation and add a comment. So actually what we have now, but then not per day, but for 7 days. So it would look like this:\r\n\r\nAgendapicker > Pick 28th june > Display: WK34 - 27th june - 3 july 2011\r\nMon 27 - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nTue 28 - Start/Endtime (ammount of hours) (or whole day enable/disable) - Vacation(enable/disable) - Commentfield\r\nWed 29 - etc..\r\nThu 30 - etc..\r\nFri 1 - etc..\r\nSat 2 - etc..\r\nSun 3 - etc..\r\n\r\nThis way they can plan more easily. Also when they press \'schedule\'  to save this planning, it should redirect to the agenda view, for the planned item\'s date (first date value at least), and set the branch/employer filter settings in overview from the planned values.');
