INSERT INTO `journal_details` VALUES ('48999','40932','attr','description','Right now in planning we can define if somedbody will work whole day. The client wants now that per branch location, they can indicate the opening hours for a branch. So for example:\r\n\r\nMon - 07:00 - 22:00\r\nTue - 09:00 - 20:00\r\netc.\r\n\r\nThen if some employer is being planned in for a specific branch on Monday (from example above), and checkbox \'whole day\' is enabled, it should plan in this user automatically from 07:00 to 22:00. Also then in planning screen when \'whole day\' is checked, the start/end time fields are disabled. System will use set hours from branch.','Right now in planning we can define if somedbody will work whole day. The client wants now that per branch location, they can indicate the opening hours for a branch. So for example:\r\n\r\nMon - 07:00 - 22:00\r\nTue - 09:00 - 20:00\r\netc.\r\n\r\nThen if some employer is being planned in for a specific branch on Monday (from example above), and checkbox \'whole day\' is enabled, it should plan in this user automatically from 07:00 to 22:00. Also then in planning screen when \'whole day\' is checked, the start/end time fields are disabled. System will use set hours from branch.\r\n\r\nAlso the branch opening hours, decide in planning screen, from what time and till what time somebody can be planned in. If the opening hours are from 07:00 till 22:00. Somebody can\'t be planned in for that branch location, from 18:00 till 23:00 for example.');
INSERT INTO `journal_details` VALUES ('49027','40956','attr','description','*Michel:*\r\n_- Right now they set per Branch the target. This is a fixed target wich is always used. But want they want, is to set this per day. So everyday they want to be able to set a different target per branch/store location. I think the best would be to have an extra \'tab\' on the leftmenu with \'Branch targets\'. So they can set per day the targets. Also they want to be able to import these targets with an Excel file (XLS)._\r\n\r\n\r\n*Bartosz:*\r\nNot sure I understood it correctly, but they want to have a possibility to set different target per branch per day. So they click on the \"Branch targets\" menu and then select a branch, then select a day and set a target for this particular branch and day. Is that right?\r\n*Michel: Yes. Although most values will be automatically imported with a file. Also in the branch editor pop-up box, we should add a tab \'Targets\'. So they can also see it there.*\r\n\r\n\r\nThen they can review the targets for each day for a branch and change it, if needed?\r\n*Michel: Yes*\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat about the situation when for a particular branch and day there\'s no custom target defined in the \"Branch targets\" tab? Should the target be taken from the \"default\" branch target field, provided on the edit branch screen?\r\n*Michel: No, this field we will remove from there. If no value set, we use standard value \'0\'*\r\n\r\n\r\nRegarding the import - what format will be the excel file? Can it be a CSV file instead of excel file or it must be XLS?\r\n*Michel: XLS is more easy for customer. If it\'s to complex we have to use CSV. Client in that case has to export self to CSV. But sometimes this exporting step gives problems. That\'s why i suggested XLS. Let me know.*\r\n\r\n\r\nQuote for this additional feature, as it wasn\'t planned at the beginning, is $100. \r\n*Michel: Approved. Add ammount to final invoice.*\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure if I will be able to finish it before 27th. Can it be 28th, Tuesday?\r\nPlease let me know if it\'s ok for you.\r\n*Michel: Would be great if we could do it for the 27th. If it\'s really not possible/unrealistic let me know.*\r\n\r\nI will give you tonight a import example file. The file will have tabs in the excelsheet. Every tab has as a name the Branchnummer. More info will follow here on this issue.','*Michel:*\r\n_- Right now they set per Branch the target. This is a fixed target wich is always used. But want they want, is to set this per day. So everyday they want to be able to set a different target per branch/store location. I think the best would be to have an extra \'tab\' on the leftmenu with \'Branch targets\'. So they can set per day the targets. Also they want to be able to import these targets with an Excel file (XLS)._\r\n\r\n\r\n*Bartosz:*\r\nNot sure I understood it correctly, but they want to have a possibility to set different target per branch per day. So they click on the \"Branch targets\" menu and then select a branch, then select a day and set a target for this particular branch and day. Is that right?\r\n*Michel: Yes. Although most values will be automatically imported with a file. Also in the branch editor pop-up box, we should add a tab \'Targets\'. So they can also see it there.*\r\n\r\n\r\nThen they can review the targets for each day for a branch and change it, if needed?\r\n*Michel: Yes*\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat about the situation when for a particular branch and day there\'s no custom target defined in the \"Branch targets\" tab? Should the target be taken from the \"default\" branch target field, provided on the edit branch screen?\r\n*Michel: No, this field we will remove from there. If no value set, we use standard value \'0\'*\r\n\r\n\r\nRegarding the import - what format will be the excel file? Can it be a CSV file instead of excel file or it must be XLS?\r\n*Michel: XLS is more easy for customer. If it\'s to complex we have to use CSV. Client in that case has to export self to CSV. But sometimes this exporting step gives problems. That\'s why i suggested XLS. Let me know.*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure if I will be able to finish it before 27th. Can it be 28th, Tuesday?\r\nPlease let me know if it\'s ok for you.\r\n*Michel: Would be great if we could do it for the 27th. If it\'s really not possible/unrealistic let me know.*\r\n\r\nI will give you tonight a import example file. The file will have tabs in the excelsheet. Every tab has as a name the Branchnummer. More info will follow here on this issue.');
