INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('40366','21622','Issue','2684','The problem was mainly connected with disabled PHP eval() function and lack of some files. Now everything works correctly.\r\n\r\nHowever there\'s one more issue with PHP warnings. PHP on the production server it\'s configured to stop on every warning - this may cause some problems in some parts of application. The more common (and less problematic) configuration is to stop only on PHP errors and disable displaying or stopping execution on PHP warnings.\r\nPlease ask hosting provider if they are able to configure the PHP server so it will only stop execution of a script on errors, not on warnings.','2011-06-27 02:59:22');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('40372','21622','Issue','1561','Bartosz Wjcik wrote:\r\n> The problem was mainly connected with disabled PHP eval() function and lack of some files. Now everything works correctly.\r\n> \r\n> However there\'s one more issue with PHP warnings. PHP on the production server it\'s configured to stop on every warning - this may cause some problems in some parts of application. The more common (and less problematic) configuration is to stop only on PHP errors and disable displaying or stopping execution on PHP warnings.\r\n> Please ask hosting provider if they are able to configure the PHP server so it will only stop execution of a script on errors, not on warnings.\r\n\r\nPassed this comment to server operator. Hope they will fix it soon for us.\r\n','2011-06-27 03:41:20');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('40376','21511','Issue','2684','Michel Michel wrote:\r\n> In system settings they want to be able to set some rules, regarding working hours calculation. Right now they have these rules:\r\n> \r\n> If you work more than 4 hours --> 30 minutes of pauze/lunch time must be taken off the total hours (so also in cash register etc)\r\n\r\nShould it work like this: user plans work in planning module and sets working hours between 9:00 - 13:30. So it will be visible as work between 9:00 - 13:30 but info about hours worked will show only 4 hours (not 4,5 hours) right? Should the same situation apply to cash register module - when user enters hours for employees?\r\n\r\n\r\n> If you work more than 9 hours --> 60 minutes of pauze/lunch time must be taken off  the total hours --> But according to Dutch rules they get 60 minutes extra. So in the end nothing changes.\r\n\r\nIt isn\'t clear to me. If the user works e.g. from 7:00 - 17:00 then he should have 10 hours worked minus 1 h pause, so hours worked should display 9 hours. How he receives 60 minutes extra and what should be the rule for it? Is it only added above 9 hours worked?\r\n\r\n> Anyway we have to implement this, because rules can change and this way we can keep it variable and easy to change.\r\n\r\nHow should it be converted to system settings? Should it be something similar to this:\r\n - Above [4] hours, add [30] minutes of pause, receive additional [ 0] minutes extra\r\n - Above [9] hours, add [60] minutes of pause, receive additional [60] minutes extra\r\n - Above [ ] hours, add [  ] minutes of pause, receive additional [ 0] minutes extra\r\n\r\netc.?','2011-06-27 04:02:32');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('40380','21511','Issue','1561','_Should it work like this: user plans work in planning module and sets working hours between 9:00 - 13:30. So it will be visible as work between 9:00 - 13:30 but info about hours worked will show only 4 hours (not 4,5 hours) right? Should the same situation apply to cash register module - when user enters hours for employees?_\r\n*Yes*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n_If you work more than 9 hours --> 60 minutes of pauze/lunch time must be taken off the total hours --> But according to Dutch rules they get 60 minutes extra. So in the end nothing changes.\r\n\r\nIt isn\'t clear to me. If the user works e.g. from 7:00 - 17:00 then he should have 10 hours worked minus 1 h pause, so hours worked should display 9 hours. How he receives 60 minutes extra and what should be the rule for it? Is it only added above 9 hours worked?_\r\n*This extra time is only added, when they work more then 9 hours. But it can be variable. What you wrote here under should actually be fine, in terms of being flexible with this rule:*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n_How should it be converted to system settings? Should it be something similar to this:\r\n- Above [4] hours, add [30] minutes of pause, receive additional [ 0] minutes extra\r\n- Above [9] hours, add [60] minutes of pause, receive additional [60] minutes extra\r\n- Above [ ] hours, add [ ] minutes of pause, receive additional [ 0] minutes extra_\r\n\r\n*Yes exactly this is right. So when we add 30 minutes of pause it will substract from worked hours.*','2011-06-27 04:16:25');
