INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('42349','22306','Issue','2684','Filtering is fixed now but the sorting issue is totally different problem. The status field is partially stored in the database and partially populated dynamically right before displaying it on the list. The problem is that when you try to sort the list using one of the fields, it is done currently on the DB level. So it\'s sorted by values that are stored in the DB. When we try to sort by the \'status\' field, it\'s currently sorted only by values stored in the DB, not taking into account status values like \'unavailable\' or \'sick\'.\r\nIn order to sort it properly we would need to retrieve all users stored in the DB first, then set the current status for them all and then sort them using PHP. This all may slow down the whole process. The question is - do we need such feature or can I just disable the sorting for \'status\' field?','2011-07-06 01:37:40');
