INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('42823','22683','Issue','1561','Here as an attachment you see a screenshot.\r\n\r\n*On the right top we have following options:*\r\n* Upload a file\r\n* Create a new form\r\n\r\nAs an attachment you find the icons for these options.\r\n\r\nAlso in the overview we will show the available files and HTML forms. An overview can just look like http://lafu.nl/sabon/finance . But we will use following column headers:\r\n\r\n*Filename - Createdate - Filetype - Filesize -*\r\n\r\nIn case of a file upload it\'s clear what will be visible in the columns. In case of a HTML form we only show the form name (instead of filename) the createdate and for filetype: Formulier.\r\n\r\nRegarding making a new form we want to have an interface like http://www.jotform.com/. In the attachment you find an example of the tools we need. Basically just that they can create an form. Also when making a new form they must also give the form the following paramaters:\r\n* Publish start/enddate\r\n* Wich usergroups can see it\r\n* or Wich branches (locations) can see it\r\n* or Wich user can see it\r\n* To wich users the form must be sent \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen a form is clicked on, in the overview or dashboard (for all other users), they must get a pop-up/tickbox where they can fill this form in, and send it. This form must be sent by e-mail to the preset users in the form paramaters\r\n\r\n\r\n ','2011-07-08 19:54:55');
