INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('46079','24308','Issue','990','Yuri Lopukhov wrote:\r\n> Also for client 10055 it generated the invoice 3202. Client says that this is not right. For client 10055(polmai) they use one project (177) wich they expand whole the time with new subprojects, and wich has invoice grouping setting \'Monthly\'. Some time ago (in May) they created some single project (267) wich was wrong. Client then discussed with me what to do, and we adviced to delete it\'s generated invoice (from 267) and to add the (not invoiced) subprojects data to the ongoing project (177). This, so that in the monthly invoice generating the not invoiced subproject(s) from 267 would be invoiced with the ones from 177. This also happend, but now the system suddenly generates again an invoice for project 267, but of course nothing happens anymore with project 267. Do you know why it generated this?\r\n\r\nThere is still one subproject in project 2011.267 with subcode A, and because invoice was deleted, system found not invoiced subproject and created new invoice for it.\r\n\r\n','2011-07-22 15:25:23');
