INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('55066','27964','Issue','3626','What is the condition to hard save. \r\nI mean, cashregister is saved on every step every time (now work like that), when we should hard-save all data ? On status=approved ? Or maybe stop to save on each step when today-date is different from already saved casheregister, so old cashregister will be not editable.','2011-09-02 18:17:39');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('55067','27964','Issue','1561','Leuconoe S&H wrote:\r\n> What is the condition to hard save. \r\n> I mean, cashregister is saved on every step every time (now work like that), when we should hard-save all data ? On status=approved ? Or maybe stop to save on each step when today-date is different from already saved casheregister, so old cashregister will be not editable.\r\n\r\nFor sure we should hardsave when cashregister has status \'approved\'. Also after that it should become read-only. Also when cashregister has status \'approved\', the clientcounter data should not be imported anymore for that branch+date. Because it happens often that after closing cashregister, the employers walk out of the store, and they are also counte in clientcounter data. This then affects the conversionrate and the bonus they should get.\r\n\r\nLet me know if this will solve issue.','2011-09-02 18:25:25');
